/* Created by Captain Kniples the Fourth */
/* For funsies */
/* Created 2024 10 25 for the Blue Carbon Cup 2, hosted by Huehuecoyotl22 */
/* This is a 2v2 map only (currently) */

/* 
  
  This map is designed around the idea of teams trading resources with each other (called slinging in extreme cases). 
   Teams have one player who has access to lots of gold and wood, but limited food. The other player(s) have access
   to lots of food and wood, but very limited gold. As such, they need to send each other resources to balance their economies.
   As such, "slinging" (which is an extreme case of team resource trading) should be allowed from dark age. 
   
   Specifically inspired by Rekawa Lagoon, ( http://www.mangrovesforthefuture.org/grants/small-grant-facilities/sri-lanka/phase-1-projects-lk/cultivating-bamboo-as-a-wood-substitute-to-protect-mangroves-and-control-erosion-at-rekawa-lagoon/ )
   the west cost of Malaysia, specifically around Danau Anak Laut, Twin Lagoon in the Phillippines and the Tropical Mahe Island (aerial shots are awesome) which is part of the Seychelles.

*/


/* ***********************************************************************************************
 *  A possible future edition of this map could be making it so that one of the players          *
 *  starts with more villagers than                                                              *
 *  the others. This would be easy to implement and create a different dynamic to any other map  *
 *  as one player on each team would be given a head start on all the other players              *
 *********************************************************************************************** */


